The paper deals with learning and identifying hidden Markov models (HMMs), which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper focuses on parametric-output HMMs with two aliased states, which falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computational efficiency of the algorithms used, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the simulations used to illustrate the theoretical analysis could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
